Equation (1) and the thermal transport model further furnish a clue for improving the APR efficiency. Considering that the photocarrier density is exponentially dependent on the WS2 Fermi energy, electrical gate control may be an efficient strategy to improve the APR efficiency. For instance, if Ec − EF decreases from 0.2 to 0.1 eV, then the relative carrier density may significantly increase from 0.001 to 0.027 under the same lattice temperature rise of ΔTL−WS2=10K\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
